data.name: Label4.Text
data.value: eTdsDNF validates records based on data updated during creation of etds return. For Validations on 27Q-DTAA, rates have been considered as per Finance Act 2018 Atmost care has been taken to help address DTAA, however post default notice generation from eTdsDNF please get this validated from Tax consultant

data.name: Label2.Text
data.value: The PAN Validation feature of the Software looks up the Income Tax Department's database to only verify existence of a Permanent Account Number. This feature does not ensure matching of deductee's name to the Permanent Account Number. The availability of this feature is dependent upon the availability of access to the Income Tax Department's server and the extant policies of the Income Tax Department in this regard.

data.name: lblDis3.Text
data.value: The business logic is based on TRSAPL’s interpretation of the prevailing provisions of the Income Tax Act, 1961 and Income Tax Rules made thereunder, various validations provided in File Validation Utilities provided by the Income Tax Department, study of several actual default notices and material available on websites of the Income Tax Department and the Tax Information Network of the Income Tax Department.

data.name: lblDis2.Text
data.value: The report of default notice generated by the Software contains only the probable result of such business logic and calculations and may not correspond with the actual default notice received from the Income Tax Department;

data.name: lblDis1.Text
data.value: The Software reads the details given in the eTDS text file and performs certain business logic and calculations to forecast the default notice(s) that are likely to be received in respect of the given file;
